md:name.md:partName: 'Umārah [ibn 'Alī ibn Zaydān] al-Hakamī al-Yamanī (d. 569 H [1174 CE]

md:note.div:
Digtsamling af den yeminitiske forfatter 'Umārah al-Yamanī, som var hofpoet hos de sidste fatimid kaliffer i Kairo.
Sjælden håndskrift købt af F. C. von Haven (d. 1763) i Kairo i 1763 i forbindelse med Carsten Niebuhr ekspeditionen (1761-1767).
Cod. Arab. 266

Collection of poetry by the Yemeni author 'Umārah al-Yamanī. He became the court poet of the last Fatimids in Cairo.
A rare manuscript acquired by F. C. von Haven (d. 1763 CE) in Cairo in 1763. von Haven was a member of the Carsten Niebuhr expedition (1761-1767).
